Nomad's chronicles - part 8
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
The monolith must not be destroyed.


I gathered around me the ones who thought the same. Together, we confronted the ethical council.


Looking back, I understand that our arguments, our voices, our thoughts, were not only our own.
The soft whispers we heard gave us strength, the intellectual power of a billion minds,
condensed in the field around the artifact.


The monolith did not want to be destroyed.